  "task": "Implement Adaptive Quantum-Adversarial Byzantine-Resilient State Machine Replication (v34) extending v33 by: (1) Dynamic Adversarial Topology Evolution—agents must formally prove (Coq/Isabelle with machine-checked certificates) that consensus adapts to Byzantine adversaries that continuously modify network topology (edge additions/deletions, node arrivals/departures) while simultaneously mounting adaptive quantum oracle attacks, with liveness guarantees that hold within network-diameter-dependent time bounds even when adversaries corrupt quorum-sized subsets across topology changes. (2) Composable Cryptographic Agility—provide machine-checked proofs that the protocol remains secure under post-quantum lattice-based, NIST-standardized, and quantum key distribution hybrid schemes simultaneously, with formal reduction bounds showing any attack on the composed system requires breaking all three crypto families. (3) Byzantine Equivocation Detection & Pinning—agents must implement and verify Byzantine agent detection (via signed equivocation transcripts) that provably identifies and pins f corrupted agents within f+1 rounds, with formal proofs that detection protocol itself resists Byzantine manipulation. (4) Secure Verifiable Random Function (VRF) Integration—integrate VRF for leader election with machine-checked proofs that (a) no Byzantine agent can bias leader selection by >1/n below-threshold probability, (b) VRF output predictability under quantum precomputation is bounded, (c) VRF output leakage in side-channel attacks is quantified and mitigated. (5) Cross-Layer Quantum Side-Channel Resilience—prove resilience to quantum-assisted timing, cache, and power analysis attacks that extract protocol state or cryptographic keys, with bounds on information leakage per attack vector. (6) Formal Security Composition Theorem—state and prove a single, machine-checked composition theorem that integrates proofs from (1)-(5) into a unified security statement: 'Under adaptive quantum adversaries with bounded topology evolution, corrupting ≤f nodes, the protocol achieves Byzantine agreement, liveness within Δ_max rounds, and secrecy of all long-term cryptographic material with quantified leakage bounds.'",
